8.02	The_Watermelon_Woman	The Watermelon Woman	The Watermelon Woman is a 1996 feature film by filmmaker Cheryl Dunye about Cheryl, a young black lesbian working a day job in a video store while trying to make a film about a black actress from the 1930s known for playing the stereotypical "mammy" roles relegated to black actresses during the period. It was the first feature film directed by a black lesbian.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f9/WatermelonWomanPoster.JPG/220px-WatermelonWomanPoster.JPG
